Package: gemini2
Title: A Package Utilized Probabilistic Approach to Identify Genetic Interactions from Pairwise CRISPR Screen 
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Ruitong",
           family = "Li",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "ruitong@broadinstitute.org",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9227-7191"))
Description: GEMINI2 uses log-fold changes to model sample-dependent and sample-independent effect,
	and uses a coordinate ascent approach to infer these effects. The inferred effects
	are used to score and identify genetic interactions, such as lethality and recovery.
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0)	
